summary:
Dear Taylor ❤️
I'm Sae, Japanese Swiftie💓
First of all, I just want to thank you so much that you  chose Tokyo where the your...
body:
Dear Taylor ❤️

I’m Sae, Japanese Swiftie💓


First of all, I just want to thank you so much that you chose Tokyo where the your last show in reputation era!!!!!

In 1989 era you chose Japan🇯🇵 as the first place where you performed.

This two thing is my happiness as Japanese ❣️


During this era, so many Japanese swifties flew to stadiums to see you.

Then THE LUCKY ONE MET YOU.

What an incredibly awesome era, don’t you think!?💖


You are always my role model because you have not only strong heart but also flexibility.

It can say your personality and job, it means making amazing songs.

I respect your kindness.

And I know your fans; swifties are amazing same as you.


Since this era, I have seen many art of you in your concert, SNS and anywhere 🎨

I haven’t ever seen such a creative fans ❣️

They respect each other and they are so polite.

I love this fandom and I know it is the best ❤️

I’m very looking forward to meet you in Tokyo TOMORROW❣️


Can’t wait to see you 💖💖

See you there 😘😘

summary: so 22 was supposed to be released as a single (officially) on the fifth of march 2013 (which was also my twelfth birthday) but...
body:
so 22 was supposed to be released as a single (officially) on the fifth of march 2013 (which was also my twelfth birthday) but the single release date got pushed back so it ended up officially becoming a single on the twelfth of march 2013.

however, while i was washing the dishes this afternoon i came to the realisation that when i turn twenty two the song 22 will be ten years old and that’s kinda crazy.

like i remember being twelve years old and singing ‘i don’t know about you but i’m feeling ten plus two’ because we were not twenty two yet.

in conclusion i am still in shock due to this realisation.

summary: i write a lot of songs about love and i think that’s because to me love seems like this huge complicated thing. but it seems...
body: i write a lot of songs about love and i think that’s because to me love seems like this huge complicated thing. but it seems like everyone once in a while, two people get it figured out, two people get it right. and so i think the rest of us, we walk around daydreaming about what that might be like. to find that one great love, where all of a sudden everything that seemed to be so complicated, became simple. and everything that used to seem so wrong all of a sudden seemed right because you were with the person who made you feel fearless.
